args:
In order to fulfill her calling, Zethia agrees to
accompany the emperor. But there is no time
to grieveâ€”the volcano could erupt at any
moment. Meanwhile, the prince and friends
chase the Flamewyrm in order to quell her rage.
Was nearly dying the last time not enough\nfor you, my son?
You're not my father. The true king would\nnever tear apart his own land and try to\nkill the dragons.
Fool child! When will you realize that\ndragons are the ones distorting our world\nand keeping it from perfection?
All the more reason for you to die.
Out of my way, you pathetic sack of scales!
Flamewyrm, did you just...save me?\nOr were you randomly lashing out?
Now's your chance, Zethia! This way!
Really, now. Do you think I will permit you\nto simply march out of here?
I'm thankful that you all came for me...
But I choose to go with this man.
I have a duty to fulfillâ€”one only I can do.
And there are other things only you can do,\nwhich is why our ways must part.
We will need more help to free our father\nfrom the clutches of this impostor.
You alone have the ability to form bonds\nwith multiple dragons.
It is essential that you save all of the\nworld's dragonsâ€”not just the Flamewyrm.
Forge as many pacts as you can!
Your mouth runs far too freely, girl.
The dragon is already mortally wounded.
Indeed! I can see her life's candle flicker\nand die even now.
And in her final death throes, she will\nobliterate all these rats who made the\nmistake of coming here!
Do you hear that? All of you traitors can\nperish together! Too bad, so sad...\nbut I LOVE it! Aaaaah ha ha ha!
You have what you came for, Emperor:\nthe dragon is dying, and I am yours.\nLet my brother and the others go.
Oh, have you deduced my intentions?
In that case, I presume you also know why\nI wanted you.
I carry on the will of the first Auspex, Ilia,\nwho bound the demon fast. In return,\nshe blesses me with her divine mana.
What's more, I am an Alberian princess\nwho possesses the proud blood of dragons.
I am ready for any fate.
Very well. The dragon will soon be dead.\nI need not waste any more time on trifles.
It takes more than that to stop me...\nNngh...
But the dragon sees us as the enemy now.\nWe have to calm her.
We are not your enemies, dragon!
Harle was right. The pain clouds her mind.
We will not fight you, because you are\nnot our enemy.
We came here to help you!
Help me? Why should I believe that?
Her eyes awash in sadness, the Flamewyrm gazes\nat {player_name} one last time.
Then, her wounded body shaking, she flies off\ndeeper into the cavern.
She's formidable, that's for certain.\nAnd defiant to the end.
Yet so is Aurelius. He challenged a dragon\non his own and emerged victorious!
What's the plan, {player_name}?\nDo we go after Zethia?
But we can't leave until we know the\nFlamewyrm is safe.
She rules over this volcano, which means\nit's tuned in to her feelings.
If she were to die or go berserk now?\nAfter having been wounded by a man?
The volcano would explode and wipe out\nhalf the damn continent! ...Or us, at the\nvery least, since we're sittin' inside it.
Remind me who talked me into this again?
We might already be too late, but we have\nto try and get through to her!
